item.title: John Gerard
item.dc:creator: John
item.content:encoded: John has been working in commercial video and digital production for over 10 years. He likes working with super talented people to create dope visuals and interactive experiences. Originally an offline editor in short-form commercial video, he has strong technical chops that make him a hands-on producer today. He's worked with a wide range of production companies, vfx and design studios and advertising agencies on everything from broadcast tv spots, websites, integrated media campaigns to music videos, short films, interactive installations, and other multimedia bric-a-brac. Alumnus of award winning design and production studio We Are Royale. Recently producer at creative advertising agency Achtung! mcgarrybowen & Studio Kraftwerk. He is based out of Amsterdam where he's freelancing and working on his Nederlands taalvaardigheid. For current availability drop him a line.

item.title: IOC Welcome to Sochi
item.dc:creator: John
item.content:encoded: http://vimeo.com/100858912 Got the opportunity to travel to Sochi Russia for Royale and hang out with a bunch of Olympians(!) to install an interactive social media video wall in the athlete villages for Cole & Weber United and the International Olympic Committee at the 2014 Olympic Games. It pulled realtime inspirational messages and images from social media sites across all nations (like not just Twitter Facebook, but also and ) and stitched them into an endlessly parallax scrolling mosaic of support for the athletes. Additionally, produced the mobile site for the athletes to navigate their Sochi experience. It was developed as an Android app which was preloaded onto everyone's brand new Galaxy Note 3's as a gift from Olympic sponsor Samsung, or as a mobile web app for the athletes who preferred their old phones. The above custom character video animation welcomed the teams to the next 17 days of Olympic history.
